div.p:
      TO Vindicate, and deliver my self, from the imputation of Sarcastick, bitter, too loose, & liberall speaches, agaynst the most Noble, Worthie, and Transcendant Sexe of WOMEN, (which some, knowing their own imperfect weaknesse, may apprehend to be
Calumnies, and detractiue to the whole Sexe) I here make humble Oblation;

 &, with all Reverence, present vnto your Ladiships Honorable Hands, this litle TREATISE; as a part of my Studie, in my wearisome Journie, this halfe yeare bypast, in forraygne Countreys.
